comments.body: I'll defer to Wolfgang. This would be a first. The species type locality is: Rio Sécure, Oromono, Bolivia, which seems to be some distance northwest of here. I don't have access to the species description so I can't research the etymology of the specific epithet. Could it refer to the nearby "Santa Cruz de la Sierra?"
It is the same specimen. @michael_jacobi yes the name does refer to the nearby Santa Cruz de la Sierra.
Thanks for combining into one observation. I'll edit my above comment to remove the link and request.
wow - would be a very cool addition if its indeed Bothrops sanctaecrucis

Yup, that's B. sanctaecrucis! The very thin, faded postocular stripe contrasting with the very distinct body pattern are characteristics that distinguish it from the recently described B. monsignifer, which was described from only a few tens of km away at slightly higher elevations.

Great record @mossambica!
@mossambica Congrats on an iNat first and having your head portrait be the taxon image.
